{"questionId":"14000","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows part of the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> with <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-intercept (5, 0) and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-intercept (0, 8).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/f7195d4a565ae381c6fd64a652ffd85f0e9f83fb.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-intercept of the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( {4x} \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( {4 \\times 0} \\right) = f\\left( 0 \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp; &nbsp;recognizing stretch of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{4}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> in <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-direction</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-intercept is 8&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (accept (0, 8) ) &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1 N2</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14000","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.S_4a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the y -intercept of the graph of f ( 4 x ) .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.8—Transformations of graphs, composite transformations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}